chrotron losses, but this scenario requires far lower magnetic field\nstrengths than those derived from observations in Tycho. One way to reconcile\nthese discrepant findings is through shock obliquity effects, and future\nobservational work is necessary to explore the role of obliquity in the\nparticle acceleration process.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Apr 2015 20:00:35 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 28 Oct 2015 15:59:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-12-09"}
